The paper discusses the design and implementation of personalization systems, which involves modeling an information-seeking interaction in a programmatic representation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on information retrieval and customization, which could place it in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category. The use of partial evaluation, a technique for specializing programs, suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of information systems, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) category. Finally, the paper discusses the modeling methodology for personalization, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category.
